Name: Sevenoaks St & William St, Beckenham
Description: Not only is hard to turn right into William Street. Many times you will have to wait until a train is pulling into Beckenham Railway station to be able to cross if the cars allow. On the Railway Parade side of the crossing is a petrol station and Mondays being cheap petrol day the queues for petrol flow onto William Street then bank up to the railway line. There has been many accidents in this area.

Comment 1: Cameron: i have been involved in approx 5 near miss's due to cars pulling out onto william st in front of me there is also a train crossing here most incidents are caused by impaitant drivers due to the poorly timed train schedule
Comment 2: Roslyn: William street heading east across the railway line decreases from double lanes across the railway line, into one lane (culdesac type setup) right where there is a school crossing, service station, (idiot drivers) . School crossing monitors raising the stop flag to let kids across to catch train etc., causing traffic heading east to stop right on the railway line at times. Wharf street crossing is at least only a delay for east west traffic, but this one is a disaster waiting to happen.
Comment 5: Cycle route parallel to railway, crossing William st is dangerous. Road islands, level crossing, split train station,discount petrol station. No room for a cyclist to wait in middle of road. Turning traffic, sometimes school crossing. There is too much happening here, I have nearly been knocked off my bike more than once either by misjudging traffic or driver inattention (eg indicating left and driving straight ahead).
Comment 6: J John: Very risky intersection where pedestrians cross at high risk.

Name: 30 & William St, Beckenham
Description: Coming from Kenwick Link through intersection at Albany Hwy onto William's St and you need to get into the left lane quickly to turn left into major shopping precinct is extremely dangerous as cars heading south on Albany Hwy turning left onto William's St should be made to give way instead they have a slip lane which is very dangerous for people coming through from Kenwick Link trying to get into the left lane.  It's like running the gauntlet for the sake of a giveaway sign to make it safer.

Comment 1: James: Traffic turning into william street from kenwick link and want to turn right into the traffic branch have to cross over traffic coming up albany Highway with very little distance to get in the right lane
Comment 2: Beatrice: When crossing Albany Hwy from Kenwick Link into William Street only two or three cars get across on a green light during the day, especially at peak hours.  This causes long lines of traffic waiting to cross, while left turning traffic passes through quickly.
Comment 3: Arun: This is the busiest intersection which takes you to the licencing centre and the shopping centre where the merging traffic and turning traffic all at one small corner.
Comment 5: Tammie: Albany Hwy traffic turning left into William St and Kenwick Link tragfic heading straight into William St --- there is alot of criss crossing of traffic as some want to go from the RH lane into the LH to turn into the driveway for Dept of Transport/Retravision, etc. Then you've got the drivers in the LH lane moving into the RH lane to turn into Spotlight, etc. Not many drivers want to give way or just barge across. Not set out very well
Comment 6: Sharon: Entering William St from Albany Hwy or Kenwick Link, it becomes very congested as converging motorists attempt to cross lanes to enter the carpark driveway into the shopping area around Retravision. Furthermore, the Licencing Centre is near Retravision, so there are many people doing driving tests in that area, which slows down motorists exiting the carpark. Would be good to have slip lane into carpark to reduce risk, or force/encourage all motorists to exit via the two Albany Hwy exits.
